<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="type locality">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Venezuela, Rio Manizanes, coll. Rumrich, 4.4.1990.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Valves lanceolate, dorsiventral, dorsal and ventral margins convex; ends barely protracted, rounded, or subcapitate, slightly deflected to ventral margin; length 34.5-42.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, breadth 10.0-12.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, L/B ratio 3.1-4.0; axial area linear, arched, central area indistinct to slightly rounded; striae 9-12 in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, becoming 11-12 toward ends, 1 isolated pore; 21-24 punctae in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<bibRefCitation author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Diatoms of Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 584" refId="B7" refString="Krammer, K, 2002. Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella. Diatoms of Europe 3: 1 - 584" title="Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella." volume="3" year="2002">Krammer (2002)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella tropica" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="tropica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella tropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recorded differences in the size, length/breadth ratio, and the presence of only one stigma as consistent diagnostic differences between this species and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Grunow" authorityYear="1996" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella turgidula" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="turgidula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella turgidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tuji, A" journalOrPublisher="Diatom" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="49 - 54" publicationUrl="https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/diatom1985/23/0/23_49/_pdf" refId="B22" refString="Tuji, A, 2007. Type examination and typification of Cymbella affinis Kuetz., C. turgidula Grunow and C. uenoi Skvortsov. Diatom 23: 49 - 54, https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/diatom1985/23/0/23_49/_pdf" title="Type examination and typification of Cymbella affinis Kuetz., C. turgidula Grunow and C. uenoi Skvortsov." url="https://www.jstage.jst.go.jp/article/diatom1985/23/0/23_49/_pdf" volume="23" year="2007">Tuji (2007)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the occurrence of specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Grunow" authorityYear="1996" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella turgidula" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="turgidula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella turgidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 1-3 isolated pores, which was also observed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Diatoms of Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 584" refId="B7" refString="Krammer, K, 2002. Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella. Diatoms of Europe 3: 1 - 584" title="Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella." volume="3" year="2002">Krammer (2002)</bibRefCitation>
in his material. We observed a continuum between the metric characteristics of 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella tropica" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="tropica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella tropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Grunow" authorityYear="1996" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella turgidula" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="turgidula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella turgidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, even in those characters that were considered by 
<bibRefCitation author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Diatoms of Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 584" refId="B7" refString="Krammer, K, 2002. Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella. Diatoms of Europe 3: 1 - 584" title="Diatoms of the European inland waters and comparable habitats. Cymbella." volume="3" year="2002">Krammer (2002)</bibRefCitation>
as differentiating. However, the outline was more lanceolate, the ends more protracted and slightly deflected to the ventral side, and the degree of dorsiventrality was lower in 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Krammer" authorityYear="2002" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella tropica" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="tropica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella tropica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared to 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="Grunow" authorityYear="1996" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Cymbellaceae" genus="Cymbella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cymbella turgidula" order="Cymbellales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="turgidula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Cymbella turgidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
